<HL>
   Business Brief -- Lyondell Petrochemical Co.:
   Firm Boosts Capital Budget
   On Strong Earnings Report
</HL>
<DATE>
07/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2
</SO>
<CO>
   LYO
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Lyondell Petrochemical Co. said it is boosting its 1990
capital-spending budget by $20 million, to $168 million, in
line with strong year-to-date performance.
   The Houston petrochemicals manufacturer reported
second-quarter net income of $155 million, or $1.93 a share,
compared with $103 million, or $1.29 a share, in the
year-earlier period. Revenue was $1.40 billion, compared with
$1.49 billion a year earlier.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Net for the six months was $233 million, or $2.91 a share,
compared with $237 million, or $2.96 a share, a year earlier.
Revenue was $2.89 billion compared with $2.75 billion.
   The company said the increase in its capital-spending
budget will facilitate increased production capacity and
expansions in certain areas.
</TEXT>
